UDTT (short for 'Woodangtangtang Girls') is a four-member girl group under SW Entertainment. They made their debut on April 29, 2025 with the single album "School Rush".

Announced on November 20, 2024, UDTT garnered attention for being produced by composer Yoo Il-Sang, who rose to prominence in the 1990s and 2000s, as well as consisting as members who previously competed on the reality shows My Teenage Girl, Girls' Planet 999, and Universe Ticket.

On March 25, SW Entertainment announced that pre-debut member Jung Sena would leave the group due to personal reasons.
